<?xml-stylesheet type="text/xsl" href="../assets/xml/rss.xsl" media="all"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>Adventurous Computing (Posts about shell)</title><link>https://blog.cyplo.net/</link><description></description><atom:link type="application/rss+xml" href="https://blog.cyplo.net/categories/shell.xml" rel="self"></atom:link><language>en</language><lastBuildDate>Tue, 01 Jan 2019 13:25:27 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>Nikola (getnikola.com)</generator><docs>http://blogs.law.harvard.edu/tech/rss</docs><item><title>Changing Terminal preferences in Gnome 3</title><link>https://blog.cyplo.net/posts/2014/03/29/changing-terminal-preferences-gnome-3.html</link><dc:creator>Cyryl PÅ‚otnicki</dc:creator><description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;It turns out this was not that obvious, at least for me, how to change
various profile preferences for Gnome Terminal under Gnome 3. You can go
and fetch the list of profiles this way:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class="code console"&gt;&lt;a name="rest_code_0cb4d06eb0fe4293977de44dfcd93517-1"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span class="go"&gt;~# dconf list /org/gnome/terminal/legacy/profiles:/&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a name="rest_code_0cb4d06eb0fe4293977de44dfcd93517-2"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span class="go"&gt;:b1dcc9dd-5262-4d8d-a863-c897e6d979b9/&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;p&gt;And then you can use the profile id to list and change various settings:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class="code console"&gt;&lt;a name="rest_code_96aa6c462aea4755bd5fe649d825ca36-1"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span class="go"&gt;~# dconf list /org/gnome/terminal/legacy/profiles:/:b1dcc9dd-5262-4d8d-a863-c897e6d979b9/&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a name="rest_code_96aa6c462aea4755bd5fe649d825ca36-2"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span class="go"&gt;foreground-color&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a name="rest_code_96aa6c462aea4755bd5fe649d825ca36-3"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span class="go"&gt;login-shell&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a name="rest_code_96aa6c462aea4755bd5fe649d825ca36-4"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span class="go"&gt;palette&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a name="rest_code_96aa6c462aea4755bd5fe649d825ca36-5"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span class="go"&gt;use-system-font&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a name="rest_code_96aa6c462aea4755bd5fe649d825ca36-6"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span class="go"&gt;use-theme-colors&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a name="rest_code_96aa6c462aea4755bd5fe649d825ca36-7"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span class="go"&gt;font&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a name="rest_code_96aa6c462aea4755bd5fe649d825ca36-8"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span class="go"&gt;bold-color-same-as-fg&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a name="rest_code_96aa6c462aea4755bd5fe649d825ca36-9"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span class="go"&gt;bold-color&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a name="rest_code_96aa6c462aea4755bd5fe649d825ca36-10"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span class="go"&gt;background-color&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a name="rest_code_96aa6c462aea4755bd5fe649d825ca36-11"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span class="go"&gt;audible-bell&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a name="rest_code_96aa6c462aea4755bd5fe649d825ca36-12"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;a name="rest_code_96aa6c462aea4755bd5fe649d825ca36-13"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span class="go"&gt;~# dconf write /org/gnome/terminal/legacy/profiles:/:b1dcc9dd-5262-4d8d-a863-c897e6d979b9/font "'Inconsolata for Powerline Medium 18'"&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a name="rest_code_96aa6c462aea4755bd5fe649d825ca36-14"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span class="go"&gt;~# dconf write /org/gnome/terminal/legacy/profiles:/:b1dcc9dd-5262-4d8d-a863-c897e6d979b9/login-shell true&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><category>commandline</category><category>dconf</category><category>font</category><category>gnome</category><category>gnome3</category><category>shell</category><category>terminal</category><guid>https://blog.cyplo.net/posts/2014/03/29/changing-terminal-preferences-gnome-3.html</guid><pubDate>Sat, 29 Mar 2014 22:34:21 GMT</pubDate></item></channel></rss>